WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:04.939 --> 01:06.274
Long time no see.

01:07.025 --> 01:09.778
SO-HYUN

01:23.666 --> 01:24.793
THE LATE HAN SO-HYUN

01:24.876 --> 01:26.377
WE LOVE OUR BRIGHT
AND RIGHTEOUS SO-HYUN

01:41.851 --> 01:43.186
You wanted to handle it yourself,

01:44.187 --> 01:46.815
and you handed over
crucial evidence to the police?

01:46.898 --> 01:48.525
I won't make excuses.

01:49.025 --> 01:49.943
You better not.

01:51.027 --> 01:52.821
Han Na-hyun must not make excuses.

01:54.155 --> 01:55.073
Actually,

01:55.698 --> 01:58.034
she must not do anything
to make excuses in the first place.

01:59.536 --> 02:00.745
Since she works for me.

02:02.497 --> 02:04.999
I'll pull out of all the cases
I've been in charge of

02:05.083 --> 02:07.001
and take some time to reflect on myself.

02:07.085 --> 02:08.920
You'll be moved to a different office too.

02:10.880 --> 02:11.881
You're dismissed.

02:59.554 --> 03:01.973
Sir, you have a video call
from the States.

03:02.932 --> 03:03.850
I'll be there soon.

03:27.206 --> 03:28.708
How are you feeling?

03:28.791 --> 03:30.501
<i>I heard you got crushed</i>

03:30.585 --> 03:32.170
<i>by a solo practitioner at that.</i>

03:33.630 --> 03:34.631
Father, that's--

03:34.714 --> 03:36.925
<i>Who was in charge from our side?</i>

03:38.635 --> 03:40.678
I was in charge of it myself.

03:43.348 --> 03:45.725
It takes many years to reach the top,

03:46.559 --> 03:48.436
but you can topple in an instant.

03:49.687 --> 03:50.688
I apologize.

03:50.772 --> 03:52.941
I won't let you down again.
Please trust me, Father--

03:53.024 --> 03:54.484
<i>The surgery went successfully.</i>

03:55.485 --> 03:57.403
<i>I can be discharged in a month or two.</i>

03:59.989 --> 04:01.491
That's great news, Father.

04:01.574 --> 04:03.201
I hope you come back soon…

04:03.284 --> 04:04.452
DISCONNECTED

04:52.959 --> 04:54.168
Hello.

04:54.252 --> 04:56.963
I'm here to meet Attorney Han Na-hyun.

04:57.046 --> 04:58.631
Attorney Han Na-hyun?

04:58.715 --> 05:00.091
Did you make a prior appointment?

05:00.174 --> 05:02.343
No, she wouldn't answer my calls.

05:03.511 --> 05:05.388
Her office is at the end of that hallway.

05:35.460 --> 05:36.294
What brings you here?

05:38.046 --> 05:39.088
Is this

05:39.881 --> 05:41.466
because of that evidence?

05:41.549 --> 05:44.844
Because the prosecution got the evidence
against the defendant?

05:46.929 --> 05:48.431
Why are you asking this question?

05:50.266 --> 05:52.477
What's so wrong
about an attorney losing a case?

05:53.269 --> 05:54.645
This is a bit harsh.

05:55.188 --> 05:57.899
What does it have to do with you, though?

05:57.982 --> 05:59.400
Do you pity me?

05:59.484 --> 06:00.610
Absolutely not.

06:01.611 --> 06:02.612
This case…

06:03.529 --> 06:06.532
I only won because you chose to lose.

06:09.577 --> 06:11.496
-What?
-You could've

06:12.580 --> 06:14.916
destroyed the hard disk back there.

06:29.097 --> 06:30.932
<i>You knew that evidence</i>
<i>would work against you.</i>

06:34.560 --> 06:37.188
The police arrived before I could do it.

06:38.314 --> 06:40.108
I'm busy, so please leave.

06:43.277 --> 06:44.153
Thank you.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.205
You…

06:55.164 --> 06:56.582
saved Ji-woo.

06:57.708 --> 07:00.461
I may be mistaken
or unaware of your true intentions,

07:01.337 --> 07:05.258
but it doesn't change the fact
that you saved her.

07:10.054 --> 07:11.347
I'm here to tell you that.

07:35.830 --> 07:37.206
Mother,

07:37.290 --> 07:38.958
I have something to tell you.

07:39.041 --> 07:40.668
What is it?

07:44.380 --> 07:46.841
I-rang is a little weird.

07:49.427 --> 07:50.261
What are you saying?

07:51.387 --> 07:52.889
Since a few days ago…

07:54.223 --> 07:55.516
A secret space?

07:55.600 --> 07:56.642
What? What did you say?

07:56.726 --> 07:59.395
I'm the gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!

07:59.479 --> 08:01.147
You darn dog-hole ghost!

08:01.230 --> 08:03.274
Darn dog hole?

08:04.233 --> 08:06.444
He mumbles to himself.

08:06.527 --> 08:08.863
And he acts like a gangster
who speaks in a dialect.

08:08.946 --> 08:10.239
I think he's a little--

08:10.323 --> 08:11.282
Enough.

08:12.575 --> 08:15.620
Mother, I get that you want to deny it.

08:15.703 --> 08:19.540
But playing dumb won't solve his illness.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.459
I'm not playing dumb.

08:22.752 --> 08:25.505
Bong-su, the truth is…

08:33.262 --> 08:34.931
Mister.

08:36.557 --> 08:37.558
Mister?

08:38.976 --> 08:42.063
Come on, mister.

08:43.523 --> 08:44.857
That's so distracting.

08:44.941 --> 08:48.402
Will you stop already?

08:50.738 --> 08:52.865
CLIENT: VERBALLY AGREED
ATTORNEY: SHIN I…

08:53.449 --> 08:54.867
What are you doing?

08:57.119 --> 08:58.538
I beg you.

08:58.621 --> 09:00.540
Can you please act like a human being?

09:00.623 --> 09:02.625
So, what are you doing right now?

09:04.085 --> 09:05.211
I'm writing a contract.

09:05.294 --> 09:06.796
Do we even need it?

09:06.879 --> 09:08.881
Now that I'm bound to deal with ghosts,

09:08.965 --> 09:11.300
I might as well write a contract
to prevent future trouble.

09:13.678 --> 09:15.638
You really are an attorney after all.

09:16.931 --> 09:20.226
I'd make it big in this field
if not for ghosts.

09:25.189 --> 09:26.399
"I, Shin I-rang,

09:26.482 --> 09:30.444
shall fulfill my duties as an attorney
for the amnesic ghost."

09:30.528 --> 09:33.197
"But the contract will be
terminated immediately

09:33.281 --> 09:35.658
if the ghost puts the attorney in danger."

09:35.741 --> 09:39.078
I can't risk my life
to help a ghost, you know.

09:39.161 --> 09:40.997
"If the attorney is hired
by a living client,

09:41.080 --> 09:44.667
he will put a stop to the ghost's case
and focus on the living client."

09:45.751 --> 09:47.253
This isn't fair for me at all.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.714
Even if you don't like it, cope with it.

09:49.797 --> 09:52.133
I'm the only one who can help you anyway.

09:53.217 --> 09:56.762
Are you sure that I'm dead, though?

09:56.846 --> 10:00.766
If you can't believe it, why don't you
go outside and try to slap someone?

10:02.143 --> 10:04.020
I've tried that already.

10:09.942 --> 10:10.943
I guess

10:11.944 --> 10:13.279
this is a bit heartless.

10:13.362 --> 10:14.655
…PUTS THE ATTORNEY IN DANGER…

10:15.323 --> 10:17.908
I'll take a risk if it's not too big.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.368
Fair enough.

10:20.328 --> 10:21.329
Hold on.

10:21.912 --> 10:23.122
What about being possessed?

10:25.791 --> 10:27.293
That's an absolute no.

10:28.127 --> 10:29.420
What, possession?

10:29.503 --> 10:32.006
You mean, I could possess your body?

10:34.300 --> 10:37.303
No, that's never going to happen.

10:37.386 --> 10:38.596
Don't overreact.

10:38.679 --> 10:41.057
I'm the one who suffers damage
from being possessed.

10:41.140 --> 10:43.684
I tumble, trip,
bump into stuff, and throw up.

10:43.768 --> 10:46.187
It's a total mess.

10:46.270 --> 10:49.899
And frustratingly enough,
I can't even remember what happened.

10:50.524 --> 10:52.568
You're really like the Hulk.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.445
Then, how do I possess you? When?

10:55.029 --> 10:56.280
Do I recite a spell or something?

10:56.364 --> 10:58.491
Like "Abracadabra"?

10:58.574 --> 11:00.910
Well, I'm not so sure.

11:01.410 --> 11:03.037
The ghost before you possessed me

11:03.120 --> 11:06.957
when he saw the food he liked
or heard the song he hated.

11:07.541 --> 11:08.542
The key is…

11:10.211 --> 11:11.796
human desire.

11:12.922 --> 11:15.758
The most basic and sheerest forms
of human desire--

11:15.841 --> 11:18.594
Or rage must be triggered
for a ghost to possess someone.

11:21.555 --> 11:23.015
You already told me before.

11:23.599 --> 11:24.475
Did I?

11:26.352 --> 11:29.438
So, who is it this time?

11:30.189 --> 11:31.941
I'm not sure yet.

11:32.566 --> 11:34.318
But she's in a school uniform.

11:34.402 --> 11:38.322
I checked nearby schools,
and her uniform didn't match anywhere.

11:39.949 --> 11:40.908
What about her talisman?

11:41.534 --> 11:43.077
I found it over there.

11:43.160 --> 11:44.161
Where?

11:44.245 --> 11:46.455
No, wait. Please don't touch it.

11:46.539 --> 11:47.915
There are so many attached to it.

11:47.998 --> 11:50.418
I took her talisman off. Here it is.

11:55.756 --> 11:57.633
Did you check surveillance footage
with the super?

11:57.716 --> 11:59.510
Yes, I did.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.929
But Min-ju was the last visitor,

12:02.012 --> 12:04.306
and the footage before her
was all deleted.

12:04.390 --> 12:05.891
Who is this?

12:06.642 --> 12:07.893
None of your concern.

12:10.729 --> 12:12.398
Then what about him over there?

12:21.991 --> 12:23.159
I-rang.

12:23.659 --> 12:26.328
Who were you talking to just now?

12:27.288 --> 12:28.497
Oh…

12:30.166 --> 12:31.459
I was talking to the priest.

12:32.168 --> 12:33.544
R-Right, Father?

12:35.337 --> 12:36.422
The priest…

12:40.759 --> 12:42.094
Ghosts?

12:43.471 --> 12:45.014
I know it's flabbergasting.

12:45.639 --> 12:47.099
But it's true.

12:47.183 --> 12:48.934
I-rang can see ghosts.

12:49.852 --> 12:52.688
Mother, I'm a huge fan of sci-fi movies,

12:52.771 --> 12:55.316
and I watch movies about superheroes,
supernatural powers,

12:55.399 --> 12:57.610
and even time travel except ghosts.

12:57.693 --> 12:58.861
Guess why?

12:58.944 --> 13:00.946
Because it's way too unrealistic.

13:01.030 --> 13:05.409
I know I won't be able to convince you.
Go and see for yourself.

13:07.453 --> 13:08.871
How scarily realistic.

13:08.954 --> 13:10.956
It's almost like a movie set.

14:24.864 --> 14:26.365
How may I help you?

14:27.449 --> 14:30.786
I'm here for a divorce consultation.

14:30.870 --> 14:32.037
Who is the attorney here?

14:34.623 --> 14:36.959
That's me. I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

14:37.042 --> 14:39.169
Oh, I see…

14:40.713 --> 14:42.172
You know what?

14:42.256 --> 14:44.216
I don't think I need a divorce.

14:48.679 --> 14:49.680
What on earth?

14:51.348 --> 14:52.933
Why did she just leave?

14:56.270 --> 14:57.396
Gosh, my neck hurts.

15:00.983 --> 15:03.444
Was I perhaps possessed?

15:05.279 --> 15:06.113
Nice dance moves.

15:07.990 --> 15:09.325
Geez.

15:15.164 --> 15:16.874
Be gone, Satan!

15:16.957 --> 15:17.875
Wait, no.

15:20.753 --> 15:22.087
-Bong-su.
-No.

15:29.637 --> 15:30.930
Are you feeling better?

15:34.141 --> 15:35.142
Yes, sir.

15:36.727 --> 15:39.939
It's me right now.
Your brother-in-law, I-rang.

15:42.066 --> 15:43.233
Oh.

15:43.984 --> 15:48.197
Then, where is she right now?

15:48.781 --> 15:50.199
She's behind me.

15:50.282 --> 15:51.575
Oh, I see.

15:52.242 --> 15:53.494
Nice to meet you.

15:53.577 --> 15:55.996
I'm Yoon Bong-su.

16:05.255 --> 16:07.508
Bong-su, she's a high schooler.

16:09.718 --> 16:10.594
Anyway,

16:11.553 --> 16:14.431
it's a bit frustrating
since you can't see her face.

16:15.057 --> 16:17.059
Why don't you try sketching her face?

16:17.726 --> 16:20.145
You might need it
to find out who she is anyway.

16:20.729 --> 16:22.940
That won't be easy.
I-rang had the lowest grade in art.

16:24.441 --> 16:25.651
I forgot that.

16:26.276 --> 16:27.236
Thanks for the reminder.

16:29.863 --> 16:31.031
Mister.

16:32.199 --> 16:33.492
It might work.

16:35.160 --> 16:36.078
What do you mean?

16:50.175 --> 16:51.427
All right.

17:10.195 --> 17:11.196
Great.

17:31.717 --> 17:32.801
It actually worked.

17:43.103 --> 17:44.354
Wow.

17:44.438 --> 17:48.525
SHINSEONG MIDDLE SCHOOL

17:53.197 --> 17:55.574
<i>You saved Ji-woo.</i>

17:56.742 --> 17:59.661
I may be mistaken
or unaware of your true intentions,

18:00.913 --> 18:04.541
but it doesn't change the fact
that you saved her.

18:05.667 --> 18:08.003
<i>If I keep on enduring…</i>

18:08.712 --> 18:10.839
-Ji-woo!
-Hey, guys.

18:12.132 --> 18:16.386
<i>May I be happy?</i>

18:16.470 --> 18:19.848
<i>I want to smile every day</i>

18:19.932 --> 18:23.393
<i>I want to be free of concerns</i>

18:23.477 --> 18:27.523
<i>Anyone, please tell me what I should do</i>

18:27.606 --> 18:30.484
<i>So help me</i>

18:30.567 --> 18:32.820
<i>I want to flop down…</i>

18:32.903 --> 18:39.034
<i>…I cannot sing a song that ended again</i>

18:39.576 --> 18:45.290
<i>Even if that's what everyone wants</i>

18:45.374 --> 18:46.583
<i>Please don't</i>

18:48.794 --> 18:52.381
<i>Make me any more miserable</i>

18:53.173 --> 18:56.218
<i>If you're pretending to stop me</i>

18:57.803 --> 19:00.264
<i>This is enough</i>

19:00.973 --> 19:03.475
<i>Please don't make me keep looking at you</i>

19:03.559 --> 19:06.186
<i>Because I get butterflies…</i>

19:18.991 --> 19:21.827
Dear God, please help my brother-in-law.

19:21.910 --> 19:24.997
At least for the sake of my mother-in-law,
my wife, and my family, please--

19:26.957 --> 19:29.126
M-Mother? Minister!

19:31.378 --> 19:32.963
Mother.

19:33.046 --> 19:35.632
What should we do about I-rang?

19:35.716 --> 19:36.925
He's all right.

19:37.467 --> 19:40.762
It didn't seem too dangerous.

19:40.846 --> 19:42.264
-But--
-She's right.

19:42.347 --> 19:44.516
The ghosts aren't evil,
so don't be afraid.

19:44.600 --> 19:47.394
-But--
-We won't completely let our guards down.

19:47.895 --> 19:51.398
Speaking of which, Bong-su…

19:54.109 --> 19:56.570
Can you take care of I-rang for me?

20:01.783 --> 20:02.784
Me?

20:04.369 --> 20:05.787
It won't be too hard.

20:05.871 --> 20:08.081
Just keep by his side

20:08.165 --> 20:11.293
and tell me what happens
from time to time.

20:11.919 --> 20:13.462
But I'm scared of ghosts.

20:14.338 --> 20:18.550
That's actually why
I don't watch ghost movies.

20:19.676 --> 20:21.053
Oh, dear Lord.

20:23.513 --> 20:26.433
Can't you reconsider?

20:26.516 --> 20:30.687
You're the only one I can count on.
That's why.

20:30.771 --> 20:31.605
Amen.

20:32.189 --> 20:33.815
Mother, please.

20:36.652 --> 20:37.611
Okay.

20:37.694 --> 20:39.154
I'll do my best

20:40.030 --> 20:41.615
to take care of my sweet brother-in-law.

20:42.908 --> 20:44.076
Thank you.

20:44.993 --> 20:45.953
Oh, right.

20:47.120 --> 20:50.249
Keep it from I-rang
that I'm aware of the situation.

20:51.041 --> 20:52.000
Why?

20:56.046 --> 20:57.381
-Mister.
-Geez!

20:59.174 --> 21:02.261
Can we listen to some music on our way?

21:02.344 --> 21:03.971
No, absolutely not.

21:04.054 --> 21:05.889
Are you chicken?

21:05.973 --> 21:06.848
No, I'm not!

21:07.432 --> 21:08.809
Then, why so sensitive?

21:08.892 --> 21:10.519
Wouldn't you be in my situation?

21:11.687 --> 21:15.190
Now that Bong-su knows, it'll be
a matter of time before my mom hears it.

21:16.066 --> 21:17.693
So what if she does?

21:17.776 --> 21:18.777
Then,

21:20.445 --> 21:21.363
I'd feel bad for her.

21:22.489 --> 21:25.951
Think about it. Her husband died early,
and now, her son's possessed.

21:28.495 --> 21:29.329
It's so sad.

21:30.455 --> 21:31.331
Are you crying?

21:31.415 --> 21:32.249
No, I'm not…

21:34.918 --> 21:37.004
Anyway, who is it this time?

21:37.504 --> 21:39.131
I hear it's a high school girl.

21:40.007 --> 21:41.300
Mother,

21:41.383 --> 21:43.510
I-rang even drew a sketch of her.

21:46.013 --> 21:48.140
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

21:48.724 --> 21:50.058
So…

21:50.142 --> 21:51.852
where are we headed?

21:51.935 --> 21:53.520
Where we can find out who you are.

21:54.354 --> 21:55.480
Where is that?

21:55.564 --> 21:56.940
A place

21:57.024 --> 21:59.526
full of cool teenagers
who are good at dancing.

22:14.750 --> 22:17.919
This is where I was?

22:24.760 --> 22:26.511
Excuse me.

22:27.179 --> 22:28.388
Have you perhaps

22:29.264 --> 22:30.682
seen this girl?

22:30.766 --> 22:32.601
No, I haven't.

22:37.022 --> 22:40.025
HIP FLOW ACADEMY
LIST OF STUDENTS

22:43.153 --> 22:46.114
I think your guess is way off.

22:47.032 --> 22:49.659
Maybe it's somewhere
more open and unrestricted.

23:00.128 --> 23:01.213
HONGIK UNIVERSITY STATION

23:18.605 --> 23:20.065
This is better.

23:32.994 --> 23:34.788
Have you perhaps seen this girl?

23:35.622 --> 23:37.040
I don't think so.

23:41.920 --> 23:42.963
-I'm not sure.
-No.

23:43.046 --> 23:44.464
-I don't know.
-I don't know her.

23:47.801 --> 23:48.802
Go for it!

24:14.119 --> 24:15.245
She's not bad.

25:08.715 --> 25:10.383
You were great.

25:11.426 --> 25:12.510
Let's go now.

25:14.054 --> 25:14.930
What's wrong?

25:15.013 --> 25:16.556
So what if we find out who I am?

25:17.432 --> 25:19.059
It won't bring me back to life.

25:34.741 --> 25:39.162
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

25:40.789 --> 25:41.873
I'm back.

25:41.957 --> 25:44.042
Why do you look so sour this time?

25:45.168 --> 25:46.503
It's nothing.

25:46.586 --> 25:49.089
There's just something that bothers me.

25:54.469 --> 25:55.929
Hi, I-rang. You're back early today.

25:56.012 --> 25:57.430
Welcome back.

26:02.269 --> 26:03.228
Sa-rang.

26:04.312 --> 26:06.690
Back when you were in high school,

26:06.773 --> 26:09.901
what did you do
when you felt sad or gloomy?

26:09.985 --> 26:11.278
-What?
-That's random.

26:12.070 --> 26:14.614
I… ate.

26:15.490 --> 26:17.284
-You ate?
-Goodness.

26:17.367 --> 26:20.078
Food is her mood booster.

26:20.870 --> 26:22.163
Oh, right. <i>Tteokbokki</i>.

26:22.247 --> 26:26.293
I'd have some real spicy <i>tteokbokki</i>
until I was drenched in sweat.

26:26.376 --> 26:28.628
Then, all my concerns were gone.

26:28.712 --> 26:31.006
That still applies for me, right?

26:32.632 --> 26:34.551
Mom, what are you up to?

26:34.634 --> 26:36.553
To celebrate I-rang's new business
and stuff,

26:36.636 --> 26:38.805
let's make something delicious.

26:38.888 --> 26:40.640
Sounds good.

26:40.724 --> 26:42.183
Sounds good indeed!

26:42.267 --> 26:43.852
Then, I'll make <i>tteokbokki</i>.

26:43.935 --> 26:45.770
-What? All of a sudden?
-<i>Tteokbokki</i>?

26:45.854 --> 26:46.688
Goodness.

26:50.066 --> 26:51.401
Let's give it a try.

26:53.987 --> 26:55.196
Gosh, it stings.

26:56.740 --> 26:57.574
Okay.

27:24.225 --> 27:26.144
Some green onions too.

27:30.940 --> 27:31.816
Why…

27:33.109 --> 27:34.152
Why is it so red?

27:36.571 --> 27:37.947
All right.

27:38.031 --> 27:39.699
It looks so good.

27:39.783 --> 27:41.701
-Here comes your grandma's food.
-Looks delicious.

27:41.785 --> 27:44.120
And some braised <i>galbi</i> too.

27:46.039 --> 27:47.248
Doesn't it look good?

27:58.176 --> 27:59.302
Oh, my.

27:59.386 --> 28:01.304
I-rang, your cheeks…

28:02.013 --> 28:03.431
Mom, his cheeks…

28:04.474 --> 28:07.435
Come along. Let's sit down and eat.

28:07.519 --> 28:09.729
-Come and sit down here.
-Mom?

28:09.813 --> 28:10.814
Let me.

28:14.943 --> 28:17.112
Eat up now.

28:17.195 --> 28:18.238
Enjoy.

28:24.077 --> 28:26.162
Wait. Hey, you're going to have that?

28:29.749 --> 28:30.875
Is it good?

28:32.252 --> 28:33.086
Yes.

28:33.795 --> 28:36.506
But you can't have spicy food.
Are you okay?

28:36.589 --> 28:39.134
No, I love spicy food.

28:41.177 --> 28:43.388
Uncle, why do you laugh like this

28:43.471 --> 28:45.014
with your mouth covered?

28:45.098 --> 28:46.266
It's so weird.

28:47.767 --> 28:49.936
Da-bong, it's a new meme.

28:52.355 --> 28:54.941
-Well, Bong-su.
-Yes?

28:55.024 --> 28:57.193
The meat was delivered.
Why don't you bring it in?

28:57.277 --> 28:58.987
-Well…
-Sa-rang, help him out.

28:59.070 --> 29:00.155
Sure.

29:00.238 --> 29:02.532
Honey, come on. The meat might go bad.

29:04.075 --> 29:06.911
Oh, silly me. I forgot to bring water.

29:12.459 --> 29:14.711
Show some respect, twirp.
Or do you have a death wish?

29:15.920 --> 29:18.840
Grandma! Uncle called me names.

29:18.923 --> 29:20.759
No way.

29:20.842 --> 29:22.594
Yes, he did!

29:22.677 --> 29:24.763
He said, "Do you have a death wish?"

29:24.846 --> 29:29.100
I didn't call you names.
I rather called you cute.

29:30.351 --> 29:33.521
Mom! Uncle pinched me. He pinched me hard!

29:37.192 --> 29:38.818
I hate you, Uncle.

29:39.402 --> 29:40.236
Don't eat.

29:41.362 --> 29:42.572
I will.

29:42.655 --> 29:43.490
Hands off.

29:49.370 --> 29:50.580
Thank you.

29:51.873 --> 29:53.291
What for? Don't mention it.

29:53.374 --> 29:56.252
I enjoy those dishes
on the regular anyway.

29:57.337 --> 29:59.297
I know you did it for me.

30:00.507 --> 30:03.968
But all I do is complain ungratefully.

30:06.095 --> 30:08.306
I guess I can't seem to admit

30:08.932 --> 30:11.059
that I'm dead when I'm already dead.

30:15.063 --> 30:16.022
Don't admit it.

30:16.856 --> 30:18.066
What?

30:18.149 --> 30:20.902
You looked so cool
when you were dancing earlier.

30:22.028 --> 30:23.279
What I mean is,

30:23.363 --> 30:25.448
your body may be dead,

30:28.243 --> 30:30.078
but your soul isn't.

30:37.418 --> 30:39.546
Gosh, it was spicy.

30:41.297 --> 30:42.882
Deliciously spicy.

30:45.009 --> 30:47.470
-Uncle.
-Yes?

30:47.554 --> 30:49.556
Her face looks exactly like this drawing.

30:51.182 --> 30:52.225
Da-bong,

30:52.809 --> 30:54.853
can you see her too?

30:55.478 --> 30:56.813
What? No.

30:58.982 --> 31:00.024
There isn't anyone here.

31:02.777 --> 31:05.071
I'm talking about her there.

31:12.412 --> 31:14.747
Why are you on TV?

31:24.048 --> 31:24.924
Yes.

31:25.550 --> 31:27.010
I understand.

31:27.635 --> 31:28.553
Thank you. Bye.

31:29.554 --> 31:31.055
What did they say?

31:31.931 --> 31:35.435
It's a popular audition TV show
called <i>Tomorrow Idol</i>.

31:35.518 --> 31:37.145
They have female trainees compete,

31:37.228 --> 31:40.273
and the final seven
will get to debut as an idol group.

31:42.984 --> 31:44.527
So, did they tell you her name and age?

31:44.611 --> 31:46.362
Loanne, and she's 19 years old.

31:46.446 --> 31:47.989
Do you recall anything?

31:48.072 --> 31:49.574
-Is she behind me?
-Loanne?

31:50.450 --> 31:51.618
No, nothing.

31:52.785 --> 31:54.162
Is it because it's a stage name?

31:54.746 --> 31:56.623
W-What else?

31:56.706 --> 31:58.458
D-Didn't you hear anything else?

31:59.042 --> 32:01.294
Loanne dropped out
due to personal reasons.

32:01.377 --> 32:02.795
But she was on TV earlier.

32:02.879 --> 32:04.339
It was a rerun.

32:04.422 --> 32:07.383
I might be able to hear more tomorrow
at the entertainment agency.

32:11.721 --> 32:13.306
Who wants ice cream?

32:19.520 --> 32:20.480
I do.

32:25.318 --> 32:26.152
Mom, what's with him?

32:28.905 --> 32:32.200
TAEBAEK

32:48.257 --> 32:49.258
What is it?

32:50.593 --> 32:52.387
It's about the company
of your case this time.

32:58.309 --> 33:00.853
He says to ask the company yourself
for more information.

33:01.437 --> 33:02.772
I understand.

33:09.862 --> 33:12.156
I don't think
they allow just anyone inside.

33:12.782 --> 33:13.992
Did you give them a call?

33:14.826 --> 33:15.868
I did.

33:16.452 --> 33:19.205
But they hung up
as soon as they heard the name "Loanne."

33:20.581 --> 33:21.958
Then, how will you get in?

33:22.041 --> 33:25.503
If there isn't a way, I'll make one.

33:34.470 --> 33:35.847
How may I help you?

33:37.473 --> 33:40.893
Hello, I'm Principal Attorney Shin I-rang
of Shin I-rang Law Office.

33:41.519 --> 33:43.980
I'm here for the human rights survey
on idol groups

33:44.063 --> 33:48.151
which is being conducted in collaboration
with the National Human Rights Commission.

33:54.615 --> 33:57.035
Please wait here
until the person in charge comes.

33:57.118 --> 33:58.244
Sure.

34:05.084 --> 34:06.836
Excuse me. Where is the bathroom?

34:07.420 --> 34:10.423
Oh, go around that corner
and you'll find it next to the elevator.

34:10.506 --> 34:11.799
I see. Thank you.

34:33.529 --> 34:35.323
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

34:42.997 --> 34:44.624
2-3F TRAINING ROOMS

34:47.168 --> 34:49.045
I'm here for an appointment with CEO Park.

34:49.128 --> 34:50.463
I see.

35:03.309 --> 35:05.019
This is like <i>Inkigayo</i> or something.

35:07.522 --> 35:09.941
Let's hurry up.
We have lots of work to do.

35:10.525 --> 35:11.734
Oh, right.

35:13.319 --> 35:14.153
Excuse me.

35:15.613 --> 35:17.532
Do you perhaps know who Loanne is?

35:18.449 --> 35:19.826
Why do you ask?

35:19.909 --> 35:21.285
I have a question to ask.

35:21.953 --> 35:23.287
Who are you? A reporter?

35:23.371 --> 35:24.330
No.

35:25.206 --> 35:26.666
I'm a lawyer.

35:27.834 --> 35:30.211
I'd like to hear some things about Loanne.

35:30.294 --> 35:31.629
Do you have time?

35:32.547 --> 35:33.548
Just a moment.

35:56.946 --> 35:59.365
This is about the IP-related case.

35:59.448 --> 36:02.118
And this lists
the stalkers of our artists.

36:05.329 --> 36:06.664
I see.

36:08.166 --> 36:10.585
I saw some chrysanthemums
by the entrance on my way here.

36:11.294 --> 36:12.837
Did something happen?

36:12.920 --> 36:14.422
Oh, that.

36:17.633 --> 36:23.389
Loanne, Abel, Ji-on, and I joined
that audition show from our agency.

36:23.973 --> 36:27.977
Loanne was pretty
and the best dancer among us.

36:29.645 --> 36:30.521
I knew it.

36:31.147 --> 36:32.148
Be quiet.

36:32.857 --> 36:34.567
-Excuse me?
-Oh.

36:35.193 --> 36:38.321
I meant to ask if she was a quiet girl.

36:39.405 --> 36:41.616
She wasn't.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.993
She had a rather loud voice.

36:44.869 --> 36:46.704
She was more of the leader type.

36:46.787 --> 36:47.705
Hey!

36:49.290 --> 36:50.583
Move to the left,

36:50.666 --> 36:53.920
to the right, and again to the left!
Must I keep repeating myself?

36:54.003 --> 36:55.171
Are you an idiot?

36:55.254 --> 36:58.466
Loanne was always competitive

36:58.549 --> 37:00.927
and never let things go easily, so…

37:02.929 --> 37:05.056
It's okay. Feel free to tell me.

37:07.225 --> 37:09.977
The girls found it hard to deal with her.

37:10.061 --> 37:11.854
I got confused. Sorry.

37:11.938 --> 37:13.105
Don't make excuses.

37:13.189 --> 37:14.440
I'll try it again.

37:14.523 --> 37:16.317
You're confusing us all.

37:16.400 --> 37:19.487
How will you become an idol when you can't
memorize this one easy move?

37:20.071 --> 37:22.448
You know countless people
can't even make it to debut.

37:22.531 --> 37:24.867
That's enough.

37:24.951 --> 37:27.328
Abel says she'll try.

37:27.411 --> 37:29.372
You may not know,

37:29.455 --> 37:31.624
but my life depends on this chance.

37:31.707 --> 37:33.417
This means everything to me.

37:34.752 --> 37:38.339
Hey, if you're not that desperate,

37:38.422 --> 37:40.591
stop causing harm to others
and just go home.

37:44.387 --> 37:45.304
What is it?

37:46.138 --> 37:46.973
Tearing up again?

37:49.850 --> 37:51.394
I'm sick and tired of this.

37:52.144 --> 37:53.312
You piss me off.

37:59.902 --> 38:01.570
Still, I think

38:01.654 --> 38:04.699
it was all thanks to Loanne

38:04.782 --> 38:06.909
that Abel and I got to this point.

38:06.993 --> 38:09.620
I was truly grateful to her.

38:11.539 --> 38:13.749
I had no idea she'd end up like that.

38:13.833 --> 38:16.544
You mean, she dropped out of the show?

38:17.712 --> 38:18.713
No.

38:20.715 --> 38:22.049
She killed herself.

38:25.094 --> 38:27.930
I killed myself?

38:34.395 --> 38:37.898
A trainee committed suicide
and the fans are going wild.

38:38.441 --> 38:40.901
They make protests
and even write online petitions.

38:41.986 --> 38:46.240
I'd like to sue the trolls and set
an example before it gets more serious.

38:46.324 --> 38:47.241
Is it possible?

38:47.825 --> 38:50.786
Several conditions are
required to sue someone

38:50.870 --> 38:52.872
such as defamation, slander, and insult.

38:53.706 --> 38:55.333
Let me look into it.

38:55.416 --> 38:56.417
THE LATE KIM SU-A

39:05.343 --> 39:06.886
"Kim Su-a,

39:08.137 --> 39:11.640
born June 20, 2007."

39:18.939 --> 39:20.816
-Su-a.
-Mom.

39:33.621 --> 39:35.039
I'M ON YOUR SIDE, LOANNE

39:58.312 --> 39:59.730
I-rang!

40:00.606 --> 40:03.275
Hey! What's going on, I-rang?
Why are you so drained?

40:03.359 --> 40:04.985
Are you okay?

40:06.612 --> 40:08.864
Still, I've made progress.

40:08.948 --> 40:09.865
What?

40:11.867 --> 40:13.160
Her name is Kim Su-a.

40:13.244 --> 40:15.996
She was born in 2007 in Suwon.

40:19.875 --> 40:21.919
<i>Su-a's mom was a young single mom.</i>

40:23.003 --> 40:26.340
<i>She neither had the ability</i>
<i>nor leisure to raise a child.</i>

40:29.593 --> 40:30.928
Repeat after me.

40:31.011 --> 40:33.222
Three-zero-one.

40:33.806 --> 40:35.766
Three-zero-one.

40:36.434 --> 40:40.396
Once you see Grandma,
hand this to her first. Okay?

40:44.650 --> 40:45.693
Now, go.

40:46.360 --> 40:49.447
What about you? Aren't you coming with me?

40:49.530 --> 40:50.531
I told you.

40:50.614 --> 40:53.117
I have to go far away to make money.

41:04.378 --> 41:05.379
Go.

41:14.054 --> 41:16.849
Three-zero-one.

41:16.932 --> 41:19.560
Three-zero-one.

41:24.356 --> 41:26.775
Three-zero-one.

41:28.068 --> 41:29.612
Three-zero…

41:38.662 --> 41:40.164
Mom!

41:41.582 --> 41:43.334
Mom!

41:45.377 --> 41:47.880
Where are you?

41:50.758 --> 41:53.135
Mom!

42:01.352 --> 42:02.686
Who is it at this hour?

42:05.189 --> 42:06.148
Grandma.

42:06.232 --> 42:08.901
Please help me find my mom.

42:11.737 --> 42:14.657
There, there. Come on inside.

42:21.413 --> 42:23.874
Bong-su, are you crying?

42:26.168 --> 42:28.128
It suddenly reminded me of my daughter.

42:28.879 --> 42:30.464
Sorry about that. Continue.

42:32.967 --> 42:37.012
Fortunately, her grandma
took her in warmly.

42:38.138 --> 42:41.850
<i>She got an unexpected family member</i>
<i>added to her lonely life.</i>

42:42.601 --> 42:45.479
<i>And Su-a got a reliable guardian.</i>

42:47.022 --> 42:50.901
<i>At that time, her grandma worked</i>
<i>at a diner by a construction site.</i>

42:51.485 --> 42:54.822
<i>Su-a was so mature for her age</i>
<i>that she felt sorry for her grandmother.</i>

42:56.490 --> 42:57.700
Grandma.

43:02.663 --> 43:04.957
Wait. Grandma!

43:14.300 --> 43:18.053
<i>So she started working part-time</i>
<i>as soon as she was of legal working age.</i>

43:25.102 --> 43:28.564
<i>Even if she was tired from work,</i>
<i>she'd dance in front of her grandmother</i>

43:29.732 --> 43:32.776
<i>because her grandmother enjoyed</i>
<i>watching her dance.</i>

43:36.280 --> 43:40.075
<i>One day, she happened to dance in Hongdae</i>
<i>on the way to her part-time work.</i>

43:41.910 --> 43:44.747
<i>A producer from Glory Entertainment</i>
<i>happened to see her.</i>

43:46.874 --> 43:49.752
That was how she became a trainee
at Glory Entertainment.

43:50.461 --> 43:53.172
She even got to perform on stage
in her dream audition show.

43:54.923 --> 43:57.134
WHAT KIND OF PERFORMANCE
DID THE GLORY TRAINEES PREPARE?

43:57.718 --> 43:58.844
<i>That Grade-A girl is so good.</i>

43:59.511 --> 44:01.388
<i>Loanne definitely deserves an A.</i>

44:01.472 --> 44:06.602
THE TRAINERS UNANIMOUSLY GIVE
LOANNE OF GLORY ENTERTAINMENT AN "A"

44:07.728 --> 44:10.856
<i>She also became hopeful</i>
<i>that she could support her grandmother.</i>

44:13.067 --> 44:15.069
<i>But in the midst of the audition show,</i>

44:15.694 --> 44:17.571
<i>Su-a had to keep working part-time.</i>

44:18.739 --> 44:22.701
<i>She was an acting child breadwinner</i>
<i>due to her grandmother's back injury.</i>

44:28.791 --> 44:32.419
<i>But not all her teammates</i>
<i>were as desperate as her.</i>

44:34.838 --> 44:38.509
One, two, three, four.

44:38.592 --> 44:41.595
Five, six, seven, eight.

44:41.679 --> 44:45.015
-One, two, three, four.
<i>-And Su-a was too young to understand.</i>

44:45.099 --> 44:46.058
Hey!

44:46.642 --> 44:47.726
Move to the left.

44:47.810 --> 44:50.229
To the left, not to the right!
Must I keep repeating myself?

44:50.312 --> 44:51.188
Are you an idiot?

44:51.271 --> 44:53.023
<i>I got confused. Sorry.</i>

44:53.107 --> 44:54.233
<i>Don't make excuses.</i>

44:54.316 --> 44:55.484
<i>I'll try it again.</i>

44:55.567 --> 44:57.194
<i>-You're confusing us all.</i>
<i>-In the end,</i>

44:57.277 --> 45:00.072
<i>her teammates stood up</i>
<i>and said they'd withdraw if Su-a didn't.</i>

45:00.155 --> 45:01.615
<i>Stop causing harm to others</i>
<i>and just go home.</i>

45:01.698 --> 45:03.450
This is as far as you can go this time.

45:04.076 --> 45:04.952
You'll have another chance.

45:05.953 --> 45:09.081
<i>The CEO of Glory Entertainment</i>
<i>pressed her to withdraw</i>

45:09.164 --> 45:11.208
<i>so that he could prevent bigger losses.</i>

45:19.216 --> 45:21.468
<i>The agency announced</i>
<i>that it was due to personal reasons,</i>

45:22.052 --> 45:23.137
<i>but in fact,</i>

45:23.220 --> 45:25.055
<i>she was forced to drop out.</i>

45:26.432 --> 45:29.476
Even so,
she shouldn't have killed herself.

45:30.060 --> 45:30.894
She didn't.

45:32.146 --> 45:33.981
Su-a wasn't weak.

45:34.523 --> 45:36.191
She was brave and optimistic.

45:36.900 --> 45:38.318
Besides, that day,

45:39.153 --> 45:41.196
she could never have wanted to die.

45:42.448 --> 45:44.867
I better just hurry home to see Grandma.

45:55.878 --> 45:56.962
Hello?

46:08.307 --> 46:09.641
It was my mom.

46:11.852 --> 46:14.480
She said she saw me in the audition show.

46:15.772 --> 46:16.690
But…

46:17.232 --> 46:19.401
can you guess the first thing
she said on the phone

46:19.485 --> 46:21.236
after more than ten years?

46:23.113 --> 46:24.323
What did she say?

46:25.574 --> 46:26.742
She called me pretty.

46:28.285 --> 46:29.369
She has to be crazy.

46:31.705 --> 46:33.373
Why did she call you?

46:33.457 --> 46:35.042
She wanted to meet.

46:35.626 --> 46:36.460
And?

46:36.543 --> 46:37.836
I agreed to meet her.

46:38.462 --> 46:39.922
I wanted to meet her too.

46:40.964 --> 46:43.425
She abandoned her little child
to survive alone.

46:44.009 --> 46:47.804
I was meaning to swear right to her face
when I met her again.

46:49.348 --> 46:53.060
So, when you went to the rooftop,
it wasn't to jump off?

46:53.143 --> 46:54.269
Me?

46:54.978 --> 46:56.605
Absolutely not.

46:57.189 --> 46:58.690
SAVE

46:58.774 --> 46:59.983
MOM

47:01.026 --> 47:03.278
<i>That day, I had to drop out</i>
<i>of the audition,</i>

47:04.029 --> 47:06.281
<i>but I thought I learned a big lesson.</i>

47:06.865 --> 47:08.242
MY STORY

47:08.325 --> 47:09.368
ADD TO MY STORY

47:13.539 --> 47:15.999
I AM HAPPY

47:21.255 --> 47:22.130
<i>But then,</i>

47:23.006 --> 47:24.800
<i>there was someone else on the rooftop.</i>

47:33.308 --> 47:35.185
<i>It was too dark to see their face, though.</i>

47:40.440 --> 47:42.609
<i>I heard a phone ring.</i>

47:44.152 --> 47:45.696
<i>I never heard that ringtone before.</i>

47:51.451 --> 47:53.912
PLEASE LOOK FORWARD
TO SEEING MORE OF LOANNE!

48:00.711 --> 48:03.005
D-Does this mean

48:03.088 --> 48:05.173
she was murdered?

48:05.757 --> 48:08.218
The victim herself made a clear testimony.

48:08.302 --> 48:09.636
And this is crucial evidence.

48:10.679 --> 48:13.515
But can we catch the culprit with it?

48:13.599 --> 48:16.560
It's hard to solve a case
with just a dead person's testimony.

48:16.643 --> 48:18.562
We learned that from Lee Gang-pung's case.

48:18.645 --> 48:21.481
Still, we ended up revealing the truth
behind his resentful death.

48:21.565 --> 48:24.985
But you're an attorney.

48:25.068 --> 48:26.236
This is a murder case.

48:26.320 --> 48:28.530
A murder case is for the police to handle.

48:29.114 --> 48:33.243
But all cases are bound
to reach an attorney in the end.

48:34.286 --> 48:35.370
Besides,

48:36.496 --> 48:39.708
Su-a was kind enough
to live her life to the fullest

48:39.791 --> 48:42.044
without resenting her mom
despite her tough circumstances.

48:42.753 --> 48:44.004
I can't turn a blind eye to her.

48:45.756 --> 48:46.757
Right?

48:46.840 --> 48:48.925
O-Of course.

48:49.009 --> 48:51.303
That's for sure.

48:51.386 --> 48:52.304
My mom.

48:53.555 --> 48:54.598
What is it?

48:54.681 --> 48:57.017
I was supposed to call my mom.

48:57.601 --> 48:58.685
I forgot.

49:00.145 --> 49:01.980
Her number's saved on my phone.

49:02.564 --> 49:05.359
She must be waiting for me. What do I do?

49:12.699 --> 49:14.368
KIM SU-A (LOANNE)
TRAINEE INFORMATION

49:17.537 --> 49:20.874
ADDITIONAL DETAILS:
LIVES JUST WITH HER GRANDMA

49:23.168 --> 49:25.712
ARTIST HAS DIED (AGE 19)

49:35.806 --> 49:37.265
WHO COMMITS SUICIDE

49:37.349 --> 49:39.017
MINUTES AFTER POSTING
THAT THEY'RE HAPPY?

49:53.657 --> 49:55.283
Can you make some time for me?

49:58.787 --> 50:01.623
Aren't you angry at me for stealing a look
at the investigation info?

50:02.207 --> 50:04.876
No need. I found the evidence
and resolved the case thanks to you.

50:06.795 --> 50:07.629
Is that so?

50:08.380 --> 50:10.465
Then, I'll ask you for a favor at ease.

50:12.426 --> 50:13.343
What is it?

50:14.177 --> 50:16.513
My new client is an entertainment agency.

50:19.349 --> 50:21.601
Let me hear you out
before giving you an answer.

50:22.561 --> 50:25.981
A female idol trainee
died of a fall from the company rooftop.

50:26.064 --> 50:28.442
The CEO claims that she killed herself.

50:29.151 --> 50:31.820
But her phone disappeared from the scene.

50:31.903 --> 50:34.614
Is it plausible that her phone
wasn't with her when she died?

50:34.698 --> 50:35.949
No.

50:36.032 --> 50:38.368
She wrote on her social media account
right before she died.

50:38.452 --> 50:40.829
Someone irrelevant to the case
may have picked it up.

50:40.912 --> 50:42.873
Or maybe the culprit.

50:43.749 --> 50:45.417
You think she was murdered?

50:46.710 --> 50:47.878
I'm open to the possibility.

50:49.171 --> 50:50.505
Speaking of which,

50:50.589 --> 50:53.049
can you check the criminal records
of the company employees

50:53.133 --> 50:54.468
and whoever is related?

50:55.051 --> 50:56.970
And if anyone is undergoing a lawsuit.

50:58.555 --> 51:01.099
Why go to such lengths, though?
It's not like you.

51:16.031 --> 51:16.865
Did you find it?

51:16.948 --> 51:21.453
The detective in charge said that
they didn't find any phone on site.

51:21.536 --> 51:23.246
<i>So, the culprit took it.</i>

51:23.955 --> 51:25.457
But I don't get it.

51:25.540 --> 51:28.460
They should've left the phone there
if they wanted to stage it as suicide.

51:28.543 --> 51:31.797
Maybe there was something
they wanted to hide saved on her phone.

51:32.339 --> 51:34.132
Where are they with the investigation?

51:34.216 --> 51:36.301
They already closed it.

51:36.384 --> 51:39.262
They found no traces or motives of murder.

51:39.846 --> 51:40.972
Thank you, Bong-su.

51:47.479 --> 51:48.355
Let's go.

51:49.731 --> 51:50.774
Go where?

51:51.525 --> 51:52.484
Let's go catch the culprit.

51:53.401 --> 51:55.195
We need to find the culprit
to find your phone

51:55.278 --> 51:56.488
and your mom's number.

51:57.364 --> 52:01.034
First, let's look into who was left
in the building at the time.

52:01.618 --> 52:03.912
Oh, Emma might help out.

52:03.995 --> 52:06.623
Okay. I better start with her, then.

52:09.876 --> 52:11.419
Wait for me.

52:50.417 --> 52:51.877
-Ms. Park.
-Oh, my goodness!

52:51.960 --> 52:53.044
Are you okay?

52:54.254 --> 52:56.172
I mistook you for a ghost.

52:56.256 --> 52:57.257
I'm sorry.

52:58.008 --> 53:00.552
What are you doing here, Father?

53:00.635 --> 53:02.804
I'm here to find something.

53:03.513 --> 53:04.723
Find what?

53:04.806 --> 53:07.601
The reason why I-rang is seeing ghosts.

53:08.184 --> 53:09.352
Is there a reason?

53:09.436 --> 53:10.729
Probably.

53:11.438 --> 53:13.815
Every outcome has a cause, you know.

53:14.941 --> 53:17.277
What brings you here?

53:17.861 --> 53:18.820
Oh.

53:20.572 --> 53:21.740
The truth is,

53:22.949 --> 53:27.078
I'm here to find something too.

53:28.705 --> 53:29.789
But then,

53:30.665 --> 53:34.586
come to think of it,
you might have an answer for me.

53:35.545 --> 53:36.379
Me?

53:40.592 --> 53:42.135
<i>A long time ago,</i>

53:42.218 --> 53:44.679
<i>I-rang's dad was a prosecutor.</i>

53:45.555 --> 53:47.766
<i>He was honest and steadfast.</i>

53:47.849 --> 53:49.100
<i>In other words,</i>

53:49.184 --> 53:52.270
<i>he was an inflexible prosecutor</i>
<i>who was stubborn as a mule.</i>

53:54.105 --> 53:57.108
<i>One day, he got into a car accident.</i>

53:58.026 --> 54:00.737
<i>His body tested positive for drugs.</i>

54:02.489 --> 54:04.324
<i>What dumbfounded me more was</i>

54:04.407 --> 54:06.743
<i>that they found</i>
<i>so much evidence of bribery</i>

54:06.826 --> 54:09.371
<i>-from his computer and desk.</i>
-I found it.

54:09.454 --> 54:10.830
-Did you find it?
-Yes, sir.

54:10.914 --> 54:13.917
<i>Along with his colleague's testimony,</i>

54:14.000 --> 54:17.379
<i>my husband turned</i>
<i>into a corrupt prosecutor in an instant.</i>

54:21.132 --> 54:22.801
<i>I was so angry and resentful.</i>

54:23.385 --> 54:27.097
<i>Grasping at straws,</i>
<i>I even visited a shaman.</i>

54:28.181 --> 54:29.557
And that was right here,

54:30.141 --> 54:32.185
Unit 501 of Okcheon Building.

54:34.604 --> 54:38.775
Could I be to blame
for what's happening to I-rang?

54:39.275 --> 54:40.944
Because I visited a shaman?

54:41.027 --> 54:42.153
Well…

54:43.655 --> 54:45.615
That, I can't be sure.

54:46.700 --> 54:48.994
But one thing is for sure.

54:49.077 --> 54:53.581
Your son has been a good influence
to the people around him,

54:54.582 --> 54:57.877
whether it be the dead or the living.

55:07.012 --> 55:08.388
Aren't you going in?

55:08.471 --> 55:10.473
What? Hold on.

55:11.516 --> 55:13.309
What should I tell them this time?

55:14.269 --> 55:15.478
Tax audit? National intelligence?

55:17.147 --> 55:18.565
Let's just go.

55:18.648 --> 55:21.860
There's a secret door only for artists
to avoid fans.

55:21.943 --> 55:25.947
I know the passcode and where the girls
might be right now. Come on.

55:28.616 --> 55:30.118
Why didn't you…

55:45.175 --> 55:46.217
It's nine-four-one-two.

56:00.774 --> 56:03.318
If they took your phone,

56:03.401 --> 56:05.236
it means something important
was saved on it.

56:05.320 --> 56:06.654
Does anything ring a bell?

56:06.738 --> 56:08.948
It could be a picture
or a voice recording.

56:13.161 --> 56:14.370
Nothing.

56:15.121 --> 56:18.625
Except for the lyrics and songs
I wrote in my spare time,

56:18.708 --> 56:19.667
there's nothing.

56:20.418 --> 56:23.004
What? Lyrics and songs?

56:24.339 --> 56:25.507
Yes.

56:35.266 --> 56:37.393
PROCEDURAL HISTORY

56:39.145 --> 56:40.772
CHARGE:
COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT

56:40.855 --> 56:44.442
Every time he was sued, he countersued

56:44.526 --> 56:46.194
and got acquitted each time.

56:48.154 --> 56:50.406
Is he innocent or is he just that good?

56:53.660 --> 56:56.538
They're probably
in that training room over there.

57:05.213 --> 57:06.756
That's strange.

57:06.840 --> 57:08.216
They practice here all the time.

57:13.179 --> 57:14.639
What day is it today?

57:15.348 --> 57:17.434
Today? It's Thursday.

57:18.518 --> 57:19.394
Are you serious?

57:20.311 --> 57:21.271
What is it?

57:40.623 --> 57:41.499
It's nothing.

57:42.083 --> 57:43.543
-Let's go again.
-Okay.

57:44.627 --> 57:45.753
You don't have to hide.

57:46.629 --> 57:47.672
They can't see you anyway.

57:48.590 --> 57:50.717
Oh, right.

57:51.509 --> 57:52.385
Do you…

57:53.970 --> 57:55.221
have a crush on that guy?

57:57.056 --> 57:58.057
What are you saying?

57:59.601 --> 58:01.144
Even Da-bong would be able to tell.

58:02.479 --> 58:05.398
Well, he's handsome. I give him that.

58:09.152 --> 58:10.111
Hold on.

58:11.070 --> 58:12.280
Remember what the priest said.

58:12.989 --> 58:16.367
Being possessed manifests
when their desires reach a peak.

58:17.660 --> 58:19.496
This doesn't feel good.
Let's hurry out of here.

58:23.500 --> 58:24.501
Who are you?

58:31.132 --> 58:32.008
Excuse me?

58:32.091 --> 58:33.384
I asked who you are.

58:34.052 --> 58:36.095
Not anyone can come in here.

58:36.804 --> 58:38.431
May I see your entrance pass?

58:39.891 --> 58:42.936
Please don't come close to me.

58:43.561 --> 58:44.437
What?

58:51.361 --> 58:53.780
Darn, it's too late.

59:00.954 --> 59:02.080
Hello.

59:02.872 --> 59:04.958
Is Songwriter Ko Jong-seok here today?

59:05.542 --> 59:06.501
Just a moment, please.

59:08.127 --> 59:10.463
He should be in the vocal training room.

59:10.547 --> 59:13.550
Please take the elevator
to the second floor.

59:14.133 --> 59:15.260
Thank you.

59:25.895 --> 59:27.689
Mr. Ko.

59:27.772 --> 59:29.607
Long time no see.

59:30.608 --> 59:33.361
Wait. Will you stand still there and talk?

59:34.070 --> 59:35.446
What's wrong, Mr. Ko?

59:36.030 --> 59:38.366
-It's me.
-Don't come any closer!

59:38.449 --> 59:40.410
Are you a reporter? A stalker fan?

59:42.328 --> 59:43.955
It's me, Loanne.

59:44.706 --> 59:46.583
What? Loanne?

59:47.208 --> 59:48.126
Mr. Ko.

59:48.960 --> 59:50.336
-Have you been well?
-Over here!

59:50.420 --> 59:51.588
Get this man out.

59:51.671 --> 59:54.132
-How did you get in? Let's go.
-Mr. Ko.

59:54.215 --> 59:55.633
Don't touch me!

59:55.717 --> 59:57.135
What is he saying? Hey, grab him.

59:57.218 --> 59:58.928
-Let's go.
-Ouch!

01:00:00.013 --> 01:00:02.432
All fans get criticized
because of scum like you.

01:00:02.515 --> 01:00:04.183
Send him straight to the police station.

01:00:04.267 --> 01:00:05.143
Mr. Ko!

01:00:18.948 --> 01:00:21.075
Hello? What is it?

01:00:21.868 --> 01:00:22.744
Right now?

01:00:23.328 --> 01:00:25.079
Okay, I'll be there.

01:00:25.163 --> 01:00:27.540
Mr. Ko! Wait!

01:00:30.918 --> 01:00:32.337
Will you let go?

01:00:33.338 --> 01:00:34.464
Mr. Ko!

01:00:44.641 --> 01:00:46.976
Ma'am, he's the songwriter.

01:00:55.860 --> 01:00:57.362
Excuse me. Wait!

01:01:14.420 --> 01:01:15.296
Wait!

01:01:32.522 --> 01:01:33.731
Na-hyun!

01:01:44.867 --> 01:01:46.077
<i>One thing is for sure.</i>

01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:51.082
<i>Your son has been a good influence</i>
<i>to the people around him,</i>

01:01:52.083 --> 01:01:53.793
whether it be the dead

01:01:55.002 --> 01:01:56.129
or the living.

01:02:05.680 --> 01:02:07.390
Are you okay?

01:03:52.119 --> 01:03:53.037
SPECIAL THANKS TO LAYONE

01:04:13.850 --> 01:04:16.060
I better look more into Ko Jong-seok.

01:04:16.143 --> 01:04:18.729
You were in the building
the day Loanne died.

01:04:18.813 --> 01:04:20.898
<i>-Did you perhaps meet her?</i>
<i>-No.</i>

01:04:20.982 --> 01:04:22.483
<i>I didn't even see her that day.</i>

01:04:22.567 --> 01:04:24.193
Something smells fishy for sure.

01:04:24.777 --> 01:04:25.862
<i>She saw me write songs.</i>

01:04:25.945 --> 01:04:27.113
My phone.

01:04:27.196 --> 01:04:29.991
I can't use any of Su-a's songs
if someone else knows about them.

01:04:30.074 --> 01:04:31.033
<i>She's in danger.</i>

01:04:31.117 --> 01:04:33.244
-He's trying to kill you too.
-It can't be.

01:04:33.327 --> 01:04:34.787
Give it back to me now.

01:04:34.871 --> 01:04:36.122
<i>Mister, watch out!</i>

01:04:37.498 --> 01:04:42.420
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
